The paper deals with the problem of rainbow connectivity in graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem involves finding the smallest number of colors required to edge color a graph such that it is rainbow connected, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the hardness of the problem, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT).
